# Import male data from all groups
male_Data <- read.delim2("macho_modified.csv", header = T)
View(male_Data)


#Extend data to get long
data_male <- reshape2::melt(male_Data, id.vars = "Group")
View(data_male)
hist(data_male$value)

#Remove suffixes for duplicates in collumn

data_male$variable[grep("^Control", data_male$variable)] <- "Control"
data_male$variable[grep("^Binge", data_male$variable)] <- "Binge"                                                   
data_male$variable[grep("binge.\\d+$", data_male$variable)] <- "Chronic.plus.binge"
data_male$variable[grep("^Chronic.\\d+$", data_male$variable)] <- "Chronic"

View(data_male)

#Additional to the graph

my_palette <- c("#0000ff","#ff8000","#ff0000","#00ff00")

notation <- list(cutpoints = c(0, 0.001, 0.01, 0.05, 1), symbols = c("***", "**", "*", "ns"))

my_comparisons <- list(c("Control", "Binge"),
                       c("Control", "Chronic"),
                       c("Control", "Chronic.plus.binge"),
                       c("Binge","Chronic"),
                       c("Binge", "Chronic.plus.binge"),
                       c("Chronic", "Chronic.plus.binge"))

# Define the order of the groups
group_order <- c("Control", "Chronic", "Binge", "Chronic.plus.binge")

# Convert the 'variable' variable to a factor with the specified order
data_male$variable <- factor(data_male$variable, levels = group_order)

# Filter for specific pathway - Metabolism
grouped_male_amino <- data_male[data_male$Group %in% 'Amino acid metabolism',]
grouped_male_vit <- data_male[data_male$Group %in% 'Metabolism of cofactors and vitamins',]
grouped_male_un_fatty <- data_male[data_male$Group %in% 'Biosynthesis of unsaturated fatty acids',]
grouped_male_fatty <- data_male[data_male$Group %in% 'Fatty acid biosynthesis',]
grouped_male_cys <- data_male[data_male$Group %in% 'Cysteine and methionine metabolism',]

#Filter for specific pathway - Organismal Systems
grouped_male_carbo <- data_male[data_male$Group %in% 'Carbohydrate digestion and absorption',]

#Filter for specific pathway - Human Diseases
grouped_male_zeimer <- data_male[data_male$Group %in% "Alzheimer's disease",]



#Option test for male - Kruskal Wyllis

#Statistics for Amino metabolism
grouped_male_amino%>%kruskal_test(value~variable)
## # A tibble: 1  6
##   .y.       n statistic    df     p method        
## * <chr> <int>     <dbl> <int> <dbl> <chr>         
## 1 value    20      11.3     3  0.01 Kruskal-Wallis
kruskal_male_amino <- dunn_test(grouped_male_amino, value~variable, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni")


collum_p_amino <- c(0.16, 0.183, 0.20, 0.234, 0.256, 0.286)
class(collum_p_amino)
## [1] "numeric"
amino_krus <- cbind(kruskal_male_amino, collum_p_amino)
amino_krus$p_label <- paste0("p = ", round(amino_krus$p.adj, 3))

amino_krus

#Boxplot Graph Amino Acid metabolism
n <- ggplot(grouped_male_amino, aes(x= factor(variable), y = value)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, aes(fill = variable))+
  geom_point(aes(fill= variable),position = position_jitterdodge(), shape = 21)  + 
  stat_pvalue_manual(data = amino_krus,
                     y.position = "collum_p_amino", 
                     label = "p_label", hide.ns = TRUE, bracket.size = 0.4, size = 5, family = "Times", vjust = -0.3) + 
  labs(title= "Amino Acid Metabolism", x = "", y ="Relative abundance") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = my_palette, labels = c("Control", "Chronic", "Binge", "Chronic plus binge")) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 18, face = "bold", margin = margin(b = 20), family = "Times"),
        axis.text.x=element_blank(),
        axis.text.y = element_text(angle = 0, size = 16, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 16, colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        axis.title=element_text(size=16, face = "bold", colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold", colour = "black", family = "Times"),
        strip.background = element_blank(),
        panel.background = element_blank(),
        panel.border = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
        legend.position="bottom", legend.box="vertical", legend.margin=margin(), 
        legend.title=element_blank(),
        legend.text=element_text(size=16, family = "Times"),
        plot.margin = unit(c(3,3,3,6), units = "mm")) + scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0.05, 0.33), breaks = c(0.05, 0.1,
                                                                                                              0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3)) 

print(n)

kruskal_male_zeimer <- dunn_test(grouped_male_zeimer, value~variable, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni")

collum_p_zeimer <- c(0.064, 0.065, 0.067, 0.072, 0.076, 0.079)

zeimer_all$p_label <- paste0("p = ", round(zeimer_all$p.adj, 3))
